From ad0d327824f4f32071c4551e9bbed97c854fe1fa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 04:32:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Implement design revisions: dashboard, sidebar, bids,
 estimates, CRM, settings, dark mode
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Dashboard: Make KPIs clickable (link to filtered bids views), activity feed
  items are now clickable links, upcoming bids table has sortable columns,
  status breakdown bars link to filtered views
- Sidebar: Add user profile popup with theme toggle, re-run onboarding,
  profile & settings link, and sign out. Show draft counts on estimates
  and proposals nav items
- Bids: Add proposed_start_date field to type and bid detail (5-column grid),
  add Start Date sortable column to bids list, handle missing dates gracefully
  with italic "No date" / "TBD" placeholders
- Dark mode: Fix button contrast — .btn-primary and .btn-accent now use
  hardcoded dark backgrounds in dark mode instead of remapped --navy/--orange
  that become too light. Fix avatar backgrounds to use hardcoded #1a3a5c
- Estimates: Add separate markup + margin lines in footer (subtotal, markup,
  subtotal+markup, margin, grand total). Add "Re-evaluate Plan via AI" button.
  Add trade cost breakdown widget with percentage bars
- Settings: Full settings page with 5 tabs (General, Estimating, Integrations,
  Team, Notifications). Estimating tab has sitewide markup/margin defaults.
  General tab has company info fields
- Proposals: Enhanced detail page with AI tone controls, bid summary sidebar
  with trades and bid amount, word count, better layout
- CRM: Add search bar filtering contacts and companies, CSV import modal
  with file upload, table view for contacts with columns
- Fix hardcoded Tailwind colors (text-red-600, bg-gray-50, etc.) across
  BidStatusUpdater, GmailImportButton, ProfileEditor, TeamManager,
  GmailSyncButton, GmailDisconnectButton to use CSS custom properties
  for proper dark mode support

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_013tbGoT1accQHYjgkoTYwPM
